3/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles15-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles15-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles15.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If that wasn’t enough, Camelback also has two new Chase hydration vests and a new hip belt as well. The New Chase Race 4 ($115) includes a 1.5L hydration bladder and is meant for racing. The Chade Adventure 8 ($130) has a 2L reservoir and a lot more storage for adventure riding where less than a full hydration pack is still desired. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13.jpg\" alt=\"Camelbak Flow 2 belt\n\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Camelbak-Mule-ON-Bike-hydration-bags-bikepacking-steel-titanium-podium-bottles13-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, the Podium Flow 2 Belt gets the same revised middle bottle position as the recently revamped Podium Flow 4 Belt. The new positioning makes it easier to get the bottles in and out, and the Flow 2 will sell for $55. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.camelbak.com\" target=\"_blank\">camelbak.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/camelbak-mule-bikepacking-bags-quickflow-bladder-stainless-titanium-podium-water-bottles/\">Camelbak Straps On M.U.L.E. Bikepacking Bags, Fills Stainless &amp; Titanium Podium Bottles!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"84eb6c6c240e938f10fb2c1d116e3e93496c08178941381c3c7fb5e7334ba671","category":"Cycling"}